  <text>
      <front>
         <p>1844 March 9: ?to Broughton<note xml:id="ftn1-47" place="foot" n="47">ATL 80-038 George Petersen papers; this appears to be a rough record of his order kept by Colenso.</note>
         </p>
      </front>
      <body>
         <p>March 9/44. ordered <hi rend="italic">conditionally </hi>through Mr. N. Broughton—the following—</p>
         <p>
            <hi rend="italic">of Holtzapffel &amp; Co<lb/>  64 Cha. Cross &amp; 127 Long acre London</hi>
         </p>
         <p>1 Folio fcp. Pg. Press. with Iron Bed, chases,)<lb/>  reg. points, &amp;c, complete) 6.16.6</p>
         <p>1 12-in roller stock &amp; frame (no made roller) )<lb/>  &amp; mould for castg. roller in— )</p>
         <p>Assort. of Furniture &amp; Quoins —————— 5</p>
         <p>
            <hi rend="italic">of Watts—</hi>
         </p>
         <p>Small Pica     lower           upper           S. Caps         Ital</p>
         <p>       a               750                     50                      20              )</p>
         <p>       e               300                     40                      12              )</p>
         <p>       i               320                     40                      12              ) 1 doz. lengths</p>
         <p>       o               400                     30                      12              ) thin Brass Rule</p>
         <p>       u               250                     15                      12              )</p>
         <p>       h               150                     30                      12              ) 6lbs pg.</p>
         <p>       k               500                     60                      12              )  Ink</p>
         <p>       m               100                     15                      10              )</p>
         <p>       n               220                     30                      10              ) 4 ream</p>
         <p>       p                 70                    15                      10              ) fcp. ptg.</p>
         <p>       r               220                     30                      12              ) paper</p>
         <p>       t               320                     30                      12              ) good</p>
         <p>       w               100                     15                      10              )</p>
         <p>       g               120                     15                      12              )</p>
         <p>Figures, stops—1-m rules, quads. &amp; spaces, as accord. to Eng. Tariff for Type of simr. weight</p>
         <p>10 lts. S.P. Italic upper &amp; lower same sorts only as above &amp; accord. to above run of Letters</p>
         <p>200 10m leads—200, 20m leads—4to pica</p>
      </body>
